en: [Entries from the Cherokee Supreme Court Docket, 1823-1834, New Echota] 1825 Oct. 28

This is an excerpt from the Cherokee Supreme Court docket for the years 1823 to 1834. The Cherokee Supreme Court convened annually in New Echota beginning on the second Monday in October and lasting three weeks. This excerpt is from the Friday October 28, 1825 session of court, in which a series of civil cases were heard. Entries from this Supreme Court docket cover items ch100-ch163.

body.value: Friday 28th Court convened agreeable to adjournment Present their Honors John Martin &C et cetera Jurors G George Saunders It is the opinion of the Jury that the Ratting Gourd , shall hold the contended share that Archy Fields contends for, on the Nickajack road, George Saunders, Foreman We the Jury find that Jessee E Bean is fined by default to pay Susannna Otterlifter one Hundred & two dollars for the farm said Bean bought of Said Susanna, with costs &c Judgement against Jessee E Bean Dft by default, whereas Nancy Miller was plaintiff with costs of suit. Court is adjourned untill until tomorrow 10 Oclock
